## Description

The project involves building a webpage layout for a recipe website using HTML and CSS. It includes a site-wide header with navigation links, main content divided into sections for featured and popular recipes, and a footer with copyright information.

## Features

- Responsive design for mobile and desktop screens.
- Navigation menu for easy access to different sections of the website.
- Featured recipe section highlighting a specific recipe with an image and detailed description.
- Popular recipes section displaying multiple recipe previews with images and descriptions.
- Email subscription form in the footer for users to subscribe to weekly recipes.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/your-username/codecademy-text-design.git`
2. Open the project folder in your preferred code editor.

## Usage

1. Open the `index.html` file in a web browser to view the webpage.
2. Make changes to the HTML and CSS files as needed to customize the layout and styles.
3. Test the responsiveness of the webpage by resizing the browser window or using developer tools.
4. Modify the content to add your own recipes or customize the website for your needs.

